						               													<description>In the late 2013 the Italian gaming club Dinx celebrated its tenth anniversary: to commemorate the event, the club gave every active member a tumbler and three customized engraved dice, whose 6-pane was replaced with the club logo.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Dinx &amp;amp; Dragons has been designed as a mini-game to be played with these dice. It can also be played with regular d6s.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;About the game&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In Dinx &amp;amp; Dragons players are red dragons fighting each other by claws and fangs: by rolling dice, players try to either hit the opponent or parry his blows.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each time an attack is successful, that player steals (and possibly eats) a candy from the opponent&amp;rsquo;s pool, thus reducing his hit points.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;As a player runs out of candies, he&amp;rsquo;s out of the game: the last player with candies in his pool is the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
